== Potato Wedges ==

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Toss on a #baking sheet{} with a
large drizzle of @oil{}, @Southwest Spice Blend{1%tsp}, @salt{}, and
@pepper{}. (You'll use the rest of the Southwest Spice Blend later.)

Roast on top rack until lightly browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

== Pickled Onion ==

While potatoes roast, halve, peel, and very thinly slice ¼ of the @red onion{1};
finely chop remaining. Quarter @lime{1}. Halve @brioche buns{2}.

In a small #microwave-safe bowl{}, combine sliced onion, juice from half the
lime (use the rest of the lime as you like), @sugar{1/4%tsp}, and a pinch of
@salt{}. Microwave until onion is softened, ~{1%minute}. Set aside.

== BBQ Sauce Mixture ==

In a second #small bowl{}, combine @BBQ sauce{4%tbsp}, @ketchup{1}, @mushroom
stock concentrate{1}, @cornstarch{1/2%tbsp}, remaining @Southwest Spice Blend{1%tsp},
and @water{1%tbsp}.

== Messy Janes ==

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tbsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high
heat. Add chopped onion; cook, stirring, until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Add @ground plant-based protein{6%ounce}; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.
Using a #spatula{}, press into an even layer; cook, undisturbed, until browned
on bottom, ~{3-4%minutes}.

> Ground Plant-Based Protein is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.

Break up protein into pieces and continue cooking until browned and warmed
through, ~{3-4%minutes} more.

Add @water{2%tbsp} to pan with plant-based protein, then stir in BBQ sauce
mixture. Cook, stirring, until sauce has thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}. (TIP: If
sauce seems too thick, add another splash of water.) Taste and season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}. Turn off heat.

Meanwhile, toast buns until golden brown.

== Assembly ==

Divide buns between plates; spread cut sides of bottom buns with
@vegan chipotle mayonnaise{2%tbsp}. Fill buns with messy jane filling and as
much pickled onion (draining first) as you like. Serve with potato wedges on
the side and any remaining mayo for dipping.

> We'd still highly recommend keeping a few napkins nearby, though.